{"questionId":"10992","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Ethyne, C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>2</sub>, reacts with oxygen in welding torches.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Ethyne reacts with steam.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>2</sub> (g) + H<sub>2</sub>O (g) → C<sub>2</sub>H<sub>4</sub>O (g)</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Two possible products are:</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><img style=\"margin-right:auto;margin-left:auto;display:block;\" src=\"__IMG__/5f1011b29505261590600595b648a581feb2c530.png\" width=\"317\" height=\"189\"></span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">State the name of product <strong>B</strong>, applying IUPAC rules.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">ethanal&nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>","meta":{"questionId":"10992","referenceCode":"19M.2.sl.TZ2.1c(ii)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"State the name of product B, applying IUPAC rules.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"c(ii)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry","10.1 Fundamentals of organic chemistry","Core","Topic 10: Organic chemistry"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}